Nigerians, celebrities and politicians alike have reacted to the tragic death of Dr. Chinelo Megafu. Dr. Chinelo was among the many passengers shot dead by terrorists as they travelled from Abuja to Kaduna on board the ill-fated commercial train. Gunmen suspected to be terrorists bombed the Abuja-Kaduna train between Katari and Rigina axis on Monday night leaving hundreds of passengers dead in the attack. As DAILY POST captured it, many passengers were said to have been initially kidnapped including the Zamfara State former deputy Governor, Mallam Ibrahim Wakkala Liman, during the deadly attack. Dr. Chinelo, a popular presence on Twitter, was among those who were shot dead as an unascertained number of passengers also sustained various degrees of injury as a result of gunshots.  What made Dr. Chineloâ€™s death more heart-shattering was that before she died, she was able to raise her voice calling for prayers on Twitter. However, instead of prayers, she received some derogatory comments from those, many Twitter users have described, as â€˜Igbophobic.â€™ Reacting to this, a former lawmaker, Shehu Sani, said â€œDr Chineloâ€™s last tweet is a powerful and angelic phrase that will forever remind us of all the victims and their tragic experiences. â€œWe all need to wear a T-shirt with the quotation of Dr Chinelo Megafuâ€™s last tweet.â€ Mr Macaroni tweeted, â€œThose same set of people that attacked the late Chinelo are the same set that attacked and trolled me when the police brutalized me. These are sycophants who are loyal only to their political gods. They care not for this country and have no conscience whatsoever left in them. Mr. P of the PSquare band tweeted, â€œWe complain about the old people in power! But we the young people how far? All she said was â€œPRAYER FOR MEâ€ And some evil people carry am for head!ğŸ‘ğŸ¾
